# Desktop shell UI

Authoritative detail: `specs/design/desktop-shell-patterns.md`.

## Resizable columns

- Main **Vault** / **Episodes** / **editor** workspace (**`MainWorkspaceSplit`**): **always** uses **`DesktopHorizontalSplit`** with the **center workspace** (markdown editor) as **`centerWorkspace`** (CSS **`desktop-hsplit-center-workspace`**); when **both** side panes are hidden, **`leftCollapsed`** on **`DesktopHorizontalSplit`** keeps a **0px** left column with **no** separator and **`left` null** so CodeMirror is not reparented to a different root. When **both** Vault and Episodes are open, **`DesktopVerticalSplit`** stacks them in the left column (**`vaultEpisodesStack.topHeightPx`** in **`layoutPanelsV4`**). **One** main **left column width** (persisted as **`inbox.leftWidthPx`**, mirrored to **`podcastsMain.leftWidthPx`**); **editor** is **`flex: 1`**. Do **not** reintroduce **`react-resizable-panels`** for this main split without a spec update (it used percentage remapping and caused visible **1px jitter** on window resize). Persist widths and stack heights via **`layoutStore`** (`layoutPanelsV4`), including **`notificationsInboxStack.topHeightPx`** for the **Notifications** + **Inbox** vertical stack in the shell **end** column (**`DesktopHorizontalSplitEnd`**).

## Editor Toolbar

- The **Editor Toolbar** is **`EditorWorkspaceToolbar`**: full-width chrome **above** **`MainWorkspaceSplit`** and the notifications column (**inside** **`VaultTab`**, before **`DesktopHorizontalSplitEnd`**). It includes the **Vault** toggle, **Episodes** toggle (**`MaterialIcon`**, **12px** in the toolbar glyph box), **Back / Forward**, optional **toolbar** **`PlaybackTransport`** (all transport glyphs are **Radix** at **15×15**, same as **`pane-header-add-btn__glyph`**) + now-playing title when an episode is active (not while composing), compose title + **Cancel** when composing, **Clean this note** (**`MaterialIcon` `auto_fix_high`**, **12px**; omitted while composing / no open note), **Inbox** tree toggle (**`MaterialIcon` `inbox`**, **12px**), and the **notifications** toggle. **Inbox** and **Notifications** may show a small red **`pane-header-add-btn__badge-dot`** (opaque **`1px`** border: **`--color-capture-chrome`**, or **`--color-editor-toolbar-icon-hover-bg`** on **inactive** button **`:hover`**, or **`--color-app-chrome-active-fill`** when the toggle is **pressed**) when there is at least one inbox markdown (via **`countInboxVaultMarkdownRefs`**) or session notification, respectively (see **`specs/design/desktop-shell-patterns.md`**). Toolbar **`pane-header-add-btn.icon-btn-ghost:hover`** uses opaque **`--color-editor-toolbar-icon-hover-bg`**, not translucent **`--color-icon-ghost-hover-bg`**. Pressed pane toggles use **`--color-app-chrome-active-fill`** button background (mostly white) + **`--color-app-chrome-surface`** icon (**97%** theme / **3%** white, chrome-bar match; capture-scoped selectors); **`:hover`** / **`:focus-visible`** inherit inactive shell hover. Markup: **`pane-header pane-header--editor-toolbar`**; styles in **`App.css`**. Open-note tabs render in **`WindowTitleBar`**, not in this row.

## Cursors

- Treat the desktop UI as a **desktop app**: **`cursor: default`** on **buttons**, **rail tabs**, **list rows**, and similar chrome. **Do not** use **`cursor: pointer`** for those.
- **Disabled** elements: **no** **`cursor: not-allowed`**; keep **`cursor: default`** with existing opacity / color disabled styling.
- **Exception:** **Panel separators** keep **`col-resize` / `row-resize`** (and any other explicit resize affordances).
- **Exception:** **Today Hub** read-only cell preview (`.today-hub-canvas__cell-readonly` / `.today-hub-canvas__cell-static-rich`) uses **`cursor: text`**; links inside still use pointer from markdown token CSS.
